The paper deals with the design and analysis of parallel approximation algorithms for facility-location problems, which are primarily studied in the fields of approximation algorithms and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves numerical optimization techniques, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with clustering problems, which are commonly studied in the field of data mining, indicating the possibility of it being categorized under cs.DM (Data Mining).
